contentrichtext.text: '''Hi-Q''' or '''HiQ''' has several meanings: *[[Hi-Q (game)]] is a game that involves jumping pegs over one another in a grid *[[HiQ (math software)]] is a differential analyzer application currently sold by [[National Instruments]] *[[Hi-Q (band)]] is a Romanian pop group *[[Kimberly-Clark Hi-Q]] is a U.S. high school academic quiz competition originating in Delaware County, Pennsylvania *[[Delco Hi-Q]] is an academic quiz competition in Delaware County, Pennsylvania *[[Hi-Q (production music)]] was a library of production music released by Capitol Records in the 1950s *In [[Gröûp X]]'s song ''Too Many Guys'', the lyrics make a reference to HIQ, a virus that can be caught via sexual intercourse; HIQ has also been showed many times in the Flash animation for the song; the name HIQ is most likely a parody of HIV There are also a large number of small companies named '''Hi-Q''', '''HiQ''', or '''HIQ'''. {{disambig}}
